.TH "ntb_transport_create_queue" 9 "ntb_transport_create_queue" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ntb_transport_create_queue \- Create a new NTB transport layer queue
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct ntb_transport_qp *" ntb_transport_create_queue
.BI "(void *data "  ","
.BI "struct device *client_dev "  ","
.BI "const struct ntb_queue_handlers *handlers "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "data" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "client_dev" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "handlers" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Create a new NTB transport layer queue and provide the queue with a callback
routine for both transmit and receive.  The receive callback routine will be
used to pass up data when the transport has received it on the queue.   The
transmit callback routine will be called when the transport has completed the
transmission of the data on the queue and the data is ready to be freed.
.SH "RETURN"
pointer to newly created ntb_queue, NULL on error.
